# LinkedIn MCP Server Configuration

# ============================================================================
# LinkedIn API Authentication
# ============================================================================

# Option 1: OAuth Credentials (Recommended - Automatic authentication)
# The server will automatically handle OAuth flow and cache tokens
# Get these from: https://www.linkedin.com/developers/apps
LINKEDIN_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id_here
LINKEDIN_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret_here
LINKEDIN_REDIRECT_URI=http://localhost:3000/callback

# Option 2: Manual Access Token (Alternative)
# If you already have an access token, use this instead of OAuth credentials
# LINKEDIN_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_access_token_here

# ============================================================================
# Server Configuration (Optional)
# ============================================================================

# Logging level: debug, info, warn, error
LOG_LEVEL=info

# ============================================================================
# How It Works
# ============================================================================
#
# With OAuth Credentials (Option 1):
#   1. Copy this file to .env: cp .env.example .env
#   2. Fill in your LINKEDIN_CLIENT_ID and LINKEDIN_CLIENT_SECRET
#   3. Start the server: pnpm dev
#   4. Your browser opens for LinkedIn authorization (first time only)
#   5. Tokens are cached at ~/.linkedin-mcp-tokens.json
#   6. Future runs use cached token automatically
#   7. Expired tokens are refreshed automatically
#
# With Manual Token (Option 2):
#   1. Obtain a token through LinkedIn's OAuth flow
#   2. Add it as LINKEDIN_ACCESS_TOKEN above
#   3. Start the server: pnpm dev
#   4. You handle token expiration manually
#
# ============================================================================
# Security Notes
# ============================================================================
#
# - NEVER commit this file with real credentials to version control
# - The .env file is already in .gitignore  
# - Token cache (~/.linkedin-mcp-tokens.json) has secure permissions (600)
# - Keep your CLIENT_SECRET secure and never share it publicly
# - Each user gets their own cached token (multi-user friendly)
#
# ============================================================================
